Package io.shiromi.saml.types

package io.shiromi.saml.types
The purpose of the package io.shiromi.saml.type is for defining types used by SAML, each separate YamlElement has its own type assigned to it, e.g. YamlString has a type of StringType
Version:
1.0
Author:
Shiromi

    AbstractListType<E>
    The wrapper-class AbstractListType is the backbone for list classes, e.g.
    AbstractListType.SubList<E>
     
    AbstractType<T>
    Instances of the class AbstractType represent a type value assignable to a YamlElement's value, each separate type has its own methods and implementation, however they can all be cast to GenericType as it has the parameter <T> set to Object, therefore each subtype of this class can be cast to it.
    BooleanType
    Instances of the class BooleanType have a boolean as value, therefore it carries the same functionality as boolean does, however, the operations are in written form, e.g.
    GenericListType
     
    GenericType
    Instances of the class GenericType carry a value of type Object, essentially acting as an Any type, as the same suggests, this class' sole purpose is to allow interchangeability between types and generification of types.
    ListType<E>
     
    NullType
    Instances of the class NullType all have a value of null, but can all be cast to the different types, it does not carry any special methods or has any special functionality
    NumberType
    Instances of the class NumberType carry a Number as value, meaning any numeric value Java allows, e.g.
    StringType
    Instances of the class StringType carry a value of type String and behave similar to it, as they contain a string as value and allow for easy access via similar methods of String.
